Implement R1 of s-9ymk: spec-correct SVG dimension detection.

## Implementation

In `src/diagram-canvas.js`:

1. Replace `#handleSvgDimensions` lines 286-288 with a call to a new helper `#measureSvg(svg)` that returns `{width, height}` using SVG2 / CSS intrinsic-sizing order:

```js
#measureSvg(svg) {
  // 1. Explicit width/height attrs — only if both are concrete (no %)
  const wAttr = svg.getAttribute("width");
  const hAttr = svg.getAttribute("height");
  if (wAttr && hAttr && !wAttr.includes("%") && !hAttr.includes("%")) {
    const w = parseFloat(wAttr);
    const h = parseFloat(hAttr);
    if (w > 0 && h > 0) return { width: w, height: h };
  }
  // 2. viewBox baseVal
  const vb = svg.viewBox?.baseVal;
  if (vb && vb.width > 0 && vb.height > 0) {
    return { width: vb.width, height: vb.height };
  }
  // 3. getBBox (rendered content bounds)
  try {
    const bb = svg.getBBox();
    if (bb.width > 0 && bb.height > 0) return { width: bb.width, height: bb.height };
  } catch { /* detached or unsupported */ }
  // 4. getBoundingClientRect (last resort)
  const rect = svg.getBoundingClientRect();
  if (rect.width > 0 && rect.height > 0) return { width: rect.width, height: rect.height };
  // 5. Hard fallback
  return { width: 800, height: 600 };
}
```

2. Update `#handleSvgDimensions` to call the helper:
```js
const { width, height } = this.#measureSvg(svg);
this.#setDimensionsAndScale(width, height);
```

3. Use `parseFloat` (not `parseInt`) everywhere in the chain. Drop the existing `parseInt(width, 10) || 800` coercion at line 288.

## Acceptance

- Running the failing tests from i-8w67 against the viewBox-only fixture now passes the dataset.baseWidth/baseHeight assertion (1200/400 and 600/800).
- Existing tests still pass.
- The cover-fit transform assertion may still fail until i-jxxx (cover) and i-jxxx (zoom 1.0) land — that is expected.

## Notes

- D2 SVGs in `examples/kubernetes/` are the real-world target; spot-check `Nodes/index.svg` (viewBox 0 0 1202 2468) renders at correct intrinsic size after this change.
- Do NOT change `#setDimensionsAndScale` or zoom behaviour in this issue — only the measurement helper.

