Implement R4 of s-9ymk: re-fit on viewer resize. This is the leaf — when closed it unblocks the parent epic.

## Implementation

In `src/diagram-canvas.js`:

1. Add private fields:
```js
#contentWidth = 0;
#contentHeight = 0;
#resizeObserver = null;
#resizeRaf = 0;
```

2. At the end of `#setDimensionsAndScale(width, height)`, cache:
```js
this.#contentWidth = width;
this.#contentHeight = height;
```

3. In `connectedCallback`, after iframe wiring:
```js
this.#resizeObserver = new ResizeObserver(() => {
  if (!this.#contentWidth || !this.#contentHeight) return;
  if (this.#resizeRaf) cancelAnimationFrame(this.#resizeRaf);
  this.#resizeRaf = requestAnimationFrame(() => {
    this.#resizeRaf = 0;
    this.#setDimensionsAndScale(this.#contentWidth, this.#contentHeight);
  });
});
this.#resizeObserver.observe(this);
```

4. Add `disconnectedCallback`:
```js
disconnectedCallback() {
  this.#resizeObserver?.disconnect();
  this.#resizeObserver = null;
  if (this.#resizeRaf) cancelAnimationFrame(this.#resizeRaf);
}
```

5. Feedback-loop guard: `#applyZoom` adjusts `iframeContainer` width/height and the canvas `scrollLeft/Top`. The ResizeObserver is attached to `this` (the canvas host), not the inner container — its size is governed by the parent grid layout, so internal scroll/container resizes do not retrigger it. Verify this assumption with a test (next item) and add a minimal guard if needed (e.g. early-return when intrinsic dims are already cached and viewport size is unchanged from last fit).

## Test

Add a Playwright test in `tests/diagram_canvas_fit_test.go` (or a new file if cleaner) that:
1. Loads a viewBox-only fixture.
2. Records the iframe `transform: scale(...)` value.
3. Resizes the page (e.g. `page.SetViewportSize(800, 1200)` after loading at default size).
4. Waits a frame.
5. Asserts the transform value has changed AND matches the cover-fit formula for the new viewport.

## Acceptance

- Resize test passes.
- All previously added tests still pass.
- Smoke test: drag-resize the browser window — diagram re-fits without reload.
- No console errors, no memory leaks across multi-instance teardown (open and close `<diagram-viewer>` instances if applicable).

